General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

There is also a Russian Translation of this document if you are interested here.

Why should I play this class?

Arcanist is one of the most rewarding classes with enough experience. They are consistently viewed as some of the best DPS you can bring to a party, and with recent buffs, have eclipsed even more. The Arcanist skill set is often regarded as ‘fast-paced’, and both identities require you to think on your feet while playing, which is a challenge that some players view as thrilling and fun.

How does my identity work?

Arcanist, the card user, has a card deck. See Identity Card Deck below for the list of cards you can draw.

The meter gets filled as you use skills. Different skills generate different levels of Identity meter. As the meter fills up, a card is generated. Different cards have different effects, and draw rates are weighted, meaning some cards get pulled more often than others. We do not have official sources on what the percentages are.

Typically, red Ruin skills generate the most meter per hit, and are buffed by the Specialization stat and Wealth runes. This is the main method Empress generates cards.

Additionally, you can also draw cards without filling the meter through tripods. Several skills have tripods that have a (typically 20%) chance of generating a card instantly. This is the main method Emperor generates cards.

Ruin (4 stack gimmick)

Apart from the Card Deck, Arcanist also has the Ruin identity. Blue skills have a stacking mechanic attached to it, with a maximum of 4 stacks per target. Most blue skills apply 2 stacks. The applied stacks are shown on your character, and on the target.

You can detonate the stacks applied on a target using a red Ruin skill at any stacks. Though, it is usually done at the max of 4 stacks for best damage.

Ruin damage scales off the Specialization stat, and its Identity generation scales off Specialization and any equipped Wealth runes on the Ruin skill. This is the primary playstyle of the Empress’ Grace builds.

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

Empress' Grace

Written by evv

Playstyle

Empress loosely follows a “builder-spender” playstyle. We follow the 4-stack gimmick in our class very faithfully, and all of our rotations will revolve around optimizing the 4 stack + Ruin combo.

Oversimplified, the rotation boils down to 4 stacks > Buffs > Detonate. For example:

This build has extremely high mobility, as most of her animations involve some sort of displacement, where you can see excellent Empress players dodge all patterns while not losing DPS uptime. However, despite being a Hit Master class, Empress is a melee build, and has all the drawbacks of being melee. Don’t forget she also happens to be quite squishy.

Additionally, you must be able to play around her Identity system. Without cards, we are a good class; with proper card usage, we are possibly the strongest class in the game (with some luck). There are 14 cards in the pool. You will have to get comfortable at recognising a card just from glancing at the image, and quickly plan out your next skills instantly.

But don’t worry, it isn’t as hard as it seems once you try it.

Stat Allocation

We do not have any particular breakpoints to reach. The more Specialization, the better.

Due to the high innate Crit Damage on Arcanist, Crit is important on our Necklace for optimal damage.

Gear Set

Nightmare is the only option on Empress Arcanist.

It solves our terrible mana issues, buffs all of our damage, and grants us the almighty Boundless Mana state, which provides more Identity generation and is where we do the most damage.

 Engravings

Here are the Engravings you should aim to use,

and why you would choose specific combinations of Engravings to make a build.

Mandatory

Empress’ Grace

+20/25/30% Damage to 4 Stack Ruin

When Ruin Hits restore 30% of consumed MP.

  • Extremely efficient because almost all our damage is from Ruin damage.
  • Can be ran at level 1 due to the scaling not being as strong as other engravings.

Grudge

+4/10/20% Damage

+20% Received Damage

  • Unconditional +20% damage. Mandatory engraving for all DPS classes.

Adrenaline

+0.3/0.6/1% Attack Power

per Stack

+5/10/15% Crit Rate at

Max (6) Stacks

  • Due to our high innate Crit Damage (77.5%), the efficiency of this engraving shoots out of the roof.
  • We can easily maintain our stacks from our low CDs and by activating Identity cards.
  • At 70% Crit (20 Neck, 10 Return. 40 Tripod), this engraving at Lvl 3 is worth roughly 18.5%.
  • At Lvl 2, it is roughly 11.5%.
  • With a 10% Crit synergy, it becomes 17.5% and 11.2% respectively.
  • This engraving lowers in value at 90% crit onwards. 13.2% and 10.6% at Lvl 3 and 2 respectively..

Pick One

Keen Blunt Weapon

+10/25/50% Crit Damage

10% Chance of

-20% Damage

Pros: No gameplay penalty, rune freedom

Cons: Doesn’t pair well with self-buffs. Scales worse with Cull

  • With the removal of Serendipity, this engraving becomes an option again.
  • Has slightly lower efficiency than the other engravings because it scales worse with Cull.
  • Not recommended on Serendipity builds.

Raid Captain

+10/22/45% of Bonus Move Speed as Damage

+4/8.8/18% Damage

at max Move Speed (140%)

Pros: Very high scaling, does not get diminished.

Cons: Fixed rotation, can have 0% effectiveness if not played well.

  • While we have no swiftness, our blue stacking skills have tripods that grant movement speed for a few seconds that max out this engraving. Has high damage efficiency.
  • However, if your rotation gets interrupted, you lose a lot of damage from this engraving.

Barricade

+3/8/16% Damage

While Shielded

Pros: Essentially no gameplay penalty.

Cons: Only benefits Ruin and Awakening. Locked into protection runes. You need 3-4 protection runes.

  • With the use of Protection runes, we can activate the damage bonus on all of our abilities (even our Awakening).
  • The catch? You are forced to run Protection runes and forego Wealth runes. In other words, you trade card generation for reliable damage.

Filler

Hit Master

+3/8/16% Damage to

Non-Directional Attacks

Pros: Unconditional increase, no gameplay penalty

Cons: Scales poorly, does not benefit all outgoing damage

  • Ruin detonation is neither frontal nor back attack, and thus is a non-positional type attack that is affected by this engraving.
  • Very reliable damage increase that does not require us to play any differently to maintain it.

Cursed Doll

+3/8/16% Attack Power

-25% Healing

Pros: Unconditional increase, applies to all outgoing damage

Cons: Potion penalty

  • Unconditional damage increase that affects all of our damage with a potion penalty.
  • Has diminishing returns with other Attack Power engravings (15.1% value with Adrenaline 3)

Level 2

Adrenaline

+0.3/0.6/1% Attack Power

per Stack

+5/10/15% Crit Rate at

Max (6) Stacks

  • At Lvl 2, Adrenaline is worth roughly 11.5%.

Not Recommended

Precise Dagger

+4/10/20% Crit Rate

-12% Crit Damage

  • Overall a DPS loss due to diminishing our built in Crit Damage.

Mass Increase

+4/10/18% Attack Power

-10% Attack Speed

  • Attack speed is important on Empress to cycle skills quickly and stay in Boundless Mana.

Spirit Absorption

+3/8/16% Attack Speed

and Move Speed

  • you are in the wrong neighborhood.

Notes

  • At Relic gearing (5x3 vs 4x3+2+1), all the options are nearly the same. Pick which you prefer/is cheaper to you.
  • At 5x3+1, Empress 1 is superior to all options. Provides a 7% increase. Empress 3 + Adrenaline 1 is almost 4% worse.
  • If you have a 97 stone in Ancient gearing (5x3+2), only Adrenaline 2 provides a significant (but not much) increase of 1.81%. Other options provide within 0.5% increase.
  • If you have a 99 stone, Empress 2 provides the most significant increase of 3.8%.
  • Overall, 97 stones are a sizable DPS increase in Relic, not so much in Ancient. If you are building 5x3+2, you need to ensure you are at least 1800 quality or you will be doing less than 5x3+1 with higher quality.

FAQ: Empress' Grace

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

What’s better? Emperor or Empress?

Emp > Emp

They are both very similar in damage. Our recommendation to you would be to pick the playstyle that you enjoy the most and play that. Both engravings are top tier in the current patch.

Why is Raid Captain not recommended more? Why is it all Barricade?

There are several reasons.

  1. As you get more experienced with the class, you are allowed higher DPS uptime when you don’t have RC confinements.

The biggest flaw of RC is you require your movement speed tripod active during your Ruins. Normally, this happens automatically as you always use a blue skill then a red skill.

The problem happens when you get your 4-stack, then you aren’t allowed to Ruin. Such as getting knocked down, having to do a mechanic, or just the boss briefly jumping out and back in (Hanumatan, Vykas G2, Brel G2, and just about every fight to be honest…). Now you enter a dilemma where you have to waste a blue skill to re-activate RC, or send a Ruin without full RC efficiency. If you do the former, you waste precious seconds to fit into a tight window - maybe even missing the window entirely - and you average fewer Ruins due to the wasted time reactivating your MS tripods. With the latter, you would’ve just done more with Barricade.

  1. RC borderline makes Backflush mandatory, which is also a flawed skill itself.

Backflush is inherently 2 seconds longer than Quadra Accelerate, in Arcanist terms it is an eternity.

It also has forced movement backwards, when fights are usually safer closer towards the boss. Or when a pattern is inside-safe, you end up not being able to cast it and having to wait for the pattern to end.

  1. Even if you go through all that effort, Wealth runes only offer roughly 4.77 cards over 5 minutes.

Because the reward is not game-changing, it’s far easier to keep the class simple and work on improving general uptime in raids instead.

An example of Barricade allowing higher DPS uptime

Does Cursed Doll have diminishing returns with Adrenaline?

Yes. Assuming Specialization accessories, instead of the 16% damage increase from Cursed Doll, it is only 15.4% with Adrenaline 2, and 15.1% with Adrenaline 3.

Ruin and its interactions with lvl10, lvl11, lvl12

Ruin is technically considered an “Identity”. So just like Shadowhunter Demonization and Artillerist Barrage, their damage is automatically buffed upon reaching lvl55 and lvl60 on your character. This also means that it does not matter whether your Ruin skills are levelled up to lvl11 or lvl12, as the damage increase is miniscule. In other words this class allows you to save some skill points?

Applying Barricade To Awakening

Awakening -> Spacebar -> Rain

Note how the shield from Protection is active when the Awakening lands.

Cast your awakening, then spacebar out of the animation. Pause for a moment, then cast Celestial Rain.

This only works with Celestial Rain due to the delay between casting and the skill landing. The idea is to land your Awakening in between that moment.

If timed wrongly, you will see your Awakening hit for tiny damage due to Celestial Rain consuming your 4 stack. It is recommended to do some practicing in Trixion.

When do I use the Star card?

As Boundless Mana is much better than Magick Addiction for us, the Star card is actually detrimental to our class most of the time.

Other than just using it when you’re in Magick Addiction, here are some situations where Star can be used to benefit.

  1. You know there is a big burst incoming, where you can only get one rotation off. Get into Magick Addiction for the increased damage.
  2. When your mana is nearly full and reaching Magick Addiction (>80%), and you are about to begin your cycle, use Star right after casting Celestial Rain. Because Rain has a delay before landing, doing this allows you to enjoy the cooldown reduction of Boundless Mana and the damage bonus of Magick Addiction.

Star rework when?

Holding Cards

In general, you do not want to hold any cards except for Star and Clown.

Having a card in your deck means you cannot draw the same card again. This can be a good or a bad thing. If you are holding a good card like Cull, you are losing your ability to draw more Culls per fight. Conversely, if you hold onto Star, you can prevent drawing another Star.

However, it is okay to hold onto Clown to duplicate a good card if you do not have one available.

Why Hit Master when Ruin skills are front/back attack?

Upon triggering Ruin, there are 2 instances of damage. The small number is from the Ruin skill itself (e.g Secret Garden). The large number is from the Ruin detonation.

Ruin is neither front or back, thus is a non-positional damage type, and is buffed by the Hit Master engraving. Majority of Empress’ damage comes from Ruin detonation, which is why Empress is a Hit Master class, despite certain Ruin skills having front/back modifiers on them.

Emperor

Written by cardslinger, Tripleeph, NotHaxetc, Cive

Playstyle

Order of the Emperor is a fast-paced, high-APM, mid-ranged consistent damage dealer that leans into the card draw aspect of their class identity much more compared to the stack + detonation focused playstyle of its counterpart. Emperor’s goal is to maintain as much DPS uptime as possible while quickly cycling through cards to empower your main damage rotation.

As a Swiftness stacking class, you will always have a button to press and thus should Always Be Casting. However, the cards you draw have a significant impact on both your rotation and your damage ceiling. This means that although Emperor is often described as a “spammy” or “piano” class, your decision-making and personal knowledge of boss patterns enables a high level of skill expression.

Emperor Arcanists must be extremely intimate with fight patterns and boss movements – more so than almost any other class – as the majority of their damage come from placement skills which have a delay on when their damage comes out. Compared to Empress, Emperor also has a harder time setting themselves up for coordinated burst windows.

 Checkmate Playstyle

Compared to non-Checkmate builds,  the Checkmate build utilizes the checkmate skill(duh) which is a long 3 seconds channel with a damage burst at the end of the channel, instead of Mysterious Stampede.

This build in theory can out damage 116 Emperor, but it is harder to execute in raids. While  Checkmate is a very high damaging skill, it has a 3s channeling time and the fact that it forces you to stay on monster’s back just for this single skill turns most aspiring Emperors towards the 116 build which is simpler and in many cases can and will out damage CM build.

If you’re still here and you want to have higher trix.. ceiling damage then be my guest!

So what changes?

Except the obvious fact of having  Checkmate instead of Stampede we also play 4 Dominion 2 Nightmare, and do not aim for Boundless. We do not benefit from Boundless MP state and it would be WAY harder to even get to this state since Checkmate cast time is stupidly long, compared to Mysterious Stampede which is a tap skill that can be casted twice.

Also since we need all 3 chosen tripods maxed up on Checkmate itself, we will need to adjust our tripods (but just a little bit) and gems.

Stat Allocation

We do not have any particular breakpoints to reach. The more Swiftness, the better.

Due to the high innate Crit Damage on Arcanist, Crit is important on our Necklace for optimal damage.

Gear Set

6 Nightmare is used as the most popular build because it grants the most damage at the lowest difficulty level. 6 Nightmare also provides the most card draw of the builds, and with our buffed card deck can be incredibly useful.

4 Nightmare + 2 Dominion is used because it is our highest damage efficacy gear set. Overall, this set grants us around ~10% more damage in a perfect vacuum, however this is non-realistic. In actual fights, 4NM2DOM will grant around ~2% more damage at the risk of a harder playstyle due to the additional management of the Dominion buff. Using Awakening in Boundless, proccing Conviction+Judgement, or having the Moon effect active are some examples of ways to achieve full uptime on the Dominion buff.

2 Nightmare + 4 Dominion is used if you prefer the Dominion buff but you are running into mana issues. This set is typically used in the 215 Checkmate build due to it fitting the rotation and the build not needing the CDR that Boundless mana gives. The only downside to using this set vs 6p Dominion is that you will be missing (15/18/21)% damage on your Emperor Card due to it not using mana.

6 Dominion is used because it offers similar damage as 6 nightmare at a slightly higher difficulty. This gearset will outdamage 6 Nightmare if Boundless is not being maintained for a good portion of the boss encounter, however it is very easy to run out of mana. This set also greatly increases our mobility due to the Spacebar cd reduction.

Notes

  • Cursed Doll can be used instead of Mass Increase
  • At Relic gearing (5x3), all the options for the 4th & 5th engraving are nearly the same. Pick which you prefer/is cheaper to you.
  • Why is there Hit Master in 5x3+1 CM? In theory, Hit Master loses to Cursed Doll because Checkmate is back attack and does not benefit from Hit Master.Cursed Doll and Mass Increase are additive damage meaning they don’t work well together and using them both results in around ~3% damage loss!
  • This means if we take IM+CD instead of IM+HM we will gain around 13% damage to checkmate but lose 3% of damage for every other skill. Given the fact Checkmate is around 20% of our total damage, CD would only be 0.02% better assuming you land every Checkmate tick on the back attack which is not realistic at all, so Hit Master is recommended in a 5x3+1 setup.

Rotations

116 Damage

This build focuses on staying in the Boundless Mana state for the lower cooldowns and attack speed, which allows you to squeeze in all of your damage within your Return window.

Call of Destiny and Mysterious Stampede are mainly used for card draw, and Stream of Edge is used at the start of our rotation for additional crit chance on our damage skills. Celestial Rain is only ever used with 4 stacks from Stream and/or CoD.

The main benefit to using this build over builds not listed in this guide (6 dominion, 215 without Checkmate) is that it grants the most damage within the Boundless state with the least downsides, and is very engaging to use. The main weaknesses of this build are its reliance on staying in Boundless, no mobility skills, and lack of paralysis/push immunity.

FAQ: Emperor

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

What’s better? Emperor or Empress?

Emp > Emp

In all honesty they are very similar in damage. Our recommendation to you would be to pick the playstyle that you enjoy the most and play that. Both engravings are S tier in the current patch with Emperor 116 being consistent damage, Empress being bursty damage, and 215 CM Emperor being a bit of both.

I feel like I’m not doing much damage. Why is that?

Arcana is a class that has a high ceiling and low floor. Meaning that if you put in the work to practice the rotation, learn fights and positioning, and consistently perform both those things at a high level then you will see amazing results.

Should I be spamming my cards because we are a swiftness class?

No. Our spec can safely use over half the cards as soon as you draw them, but you will want to be smart about specific cards drawn to use within your window of damage. These cards include: Cull, Twisted Fate, Wheel of Fortune, Sovereign, and Star.

When do I use the Star card?

Due to the way our Nightmare set works, you ideally do not want to use the Star card while in boundless or entering boundless, as we deal more damage by staying within the state. However, if you do draw a Star card, you can ideally use it in a few select scenarios:

  1. The boss is about to have mechanics you must do, or cannot take damage
  2. The boss is phasing and you can use 1 full rotation
  3. You are at ~500 mana after just entering Boundless

The reason for these scenarios is due to Emperor Arcana doing more damage within Boundless over long periods of time. However, with scenario 2, a full Magick Addiction rotation before the boss phases will actually be higher damage.

What is the damage difference between our different Relic builds?

(credit to Morningbear for the translation)

This is our gear efficacy chart used on Inven guides3 to help determine dps performance of the possible set combos. As mentioned above, under perfect scenarios, 4NM2Dom in Boundless is about 10% higher than any other set combination. However, this is unrealistic because it is simmed under 100% boundless and dominion uptime. Additionally, 6 Dom and 6 NM are close, however due to 6 Dom’s lower card draw, and because this table is simmed without the use of cards, realistically it will be slightly lower than 6NM. Overall, both 6NM and 4NM2Dom will perform close to each other, so go whichever gear set fits your playstyle.

Why is Celestial Rain at level 10?

Celestial Rain is kept at level 10 due to the way ruin skills work with the base skill damage. By levelling up Celestial Rain to 11 and 12, only the BASE damage of the skill gets increased, not the actual damaging part which is the ruin detonation from stacks. Think about Celestial Rain as two separate instances of damage – the base skill which does minimal damage (what happens when you use the skill with zero stacks), and the ‘detonation’ damage which causes the skill to be our 4th highest damage within our kit. That is why we use the skill points elsewhere, such as levelling up Mysterious Stampede.

How do I maintain Dominion Fang?

Under normal circumstances you can’t.

Our options include:

  1. Conviction + Judgment
  2. Moon card
  3. Wheel of Fortune

Try your best to always have at least one of the above active.

If you screw up and use your awakening outside of your judgment you will face a 28 sec downtime even with 1800 swift which is a HUGE damage loss and should be avoided at all costs!

And just because you got Wheel and used awakening with it this DOES NOT MEAN YOU HAVE TO CAST IT TWICE IN A ROW as this will quickly result in you running out of awakening usages making you useless for the rest of the raid. Wait till your dominion buff is off and THEN use another awakening.

I run out of Awakening charges during the raid?

Unfortunately this does happen when doing raids with full party being on ilvl.

If you notice that is the case, you can equip two Awakening engravings, cast your Awakening, then switch back. This activates Dominion Fang, refills your Awakening, and due to Lvl3 Awakening engraving being active during your Awakening, you will have the cooldown ready in time.

I’m not MVP

Checkmate build takes a lot of time to execute properly and is heavily depended on your tripods level. In most cases if you just started with any class, the cheapest power increase you can get is leveling up your tripods.

CM rewards player a lot for adjusting rotation on the fly depending on what the boss is doing what cards you have and what skills are not on cooldown.
